# $100,000 COUNTER-CLOAKING DETECTION RIG
Purpose: High-end law enforcement/security system to detect cloaked or camouflaged individuals.

---

## 1. Imaging Modules

### A. High-End Thermal: FLIR A6780 MWIR System — $28,000
- Sees through optical camouflage
- Detects suit heat leakage
- Confirms human signatures instantly

### B. Scientific SWIR Camera (Sensors Unlimited MicroSWIR) — $16,000
- Cloaking surfaces fail in SWIR
- Highlights reflective anomalies
- Reveals outline even at distance

### C. Dual NIR Cameras (Sony IMX sensors) — $1,800
- Detects distortion, shimmer, and panel seams

### D. Multi-Angle 8K Visible Spectrum Cameras — $3,500
- For parallax distortion detection
- AI checks perspective mismatch

---

## 2. Active Scanning Modules

### A. LIDAR Mapping System (Ouster OS1 or OS2) — $12,500
- 3D mesh shows person even when visually hidden
- Detects voids, anomalies, or reflective distortions

### B. mmWave Radar Array (Texas Instruments Industrial Radar) — $2,200
- Shows full human mass through cloaking panels
- Works through smoke, fabric, glass, fog

### C. IR & SWIR Strobe Projectors — $4,000
- Break camouflage with flood pulses
- Reveals flicker when panels can’t update fast enough

### D. Structured Light Projector (Dot Matrix) — $1,200
- Causes geometry breakup on cloaking panels

